text.__SUMMARY__: Conus saucatsensis is an extinct species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.
text.Description: The size of the shell attains 36 mm.
text.Distribution: This marine species is only known as a fossil from the Miocene found near Bordeaux, France.

Cossmann (1896). Essais de Paleoconchologie Comparee 2 p. 148 ff
